</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>), <span class=\"fn\">∀ <span class=\"fn\">x</span> ∈ <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">K</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span>, <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Pseudo/Defs.html#Metric.closedBall\">closedBall</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">δ</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#HasSubset.Subset\">⊆</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">U</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"**Alias** of `Metric.exists_contMDiffMap_forall_closedBall_subset`.\n\n---\n\nLet `M` be a smooth σ-compact manifold with a metric. Let `K : ι → Set M` be a locally finite\nfamily of closed sets, let `U : ι → Set M` be a family of open sets such that `K i ⊆ U i` for all\n`i`. Then there exists a positive smooth function `δ : M → ℝ≥0` such that for any `i` and `x ∈ K i`,\nwe have `Metric.closedBall x (δ x) ⊆ U i`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Geometry/Manifold/PartitionOfUnity.html#Metric.exists_smooth_forall_closedBall_subset","kind":"theorem","line":734,"name":"Metric.exists_smooth_forall_closedBall_subset","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Geometry/Manifold/PartitionOfUnity.lean#L734-L736"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Geometry/Manifold/PartitionOfUnity.html#Metric.exists_contMDiffMap_forall_closedBall_subset\"><span class=\"name\">Metric</span>.<span class=\"name\">exists_contMDiffMap_forall_closedBall_subset</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">ι</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> uι}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E</