lib/Topology/PartitionOfUnity.html#BumpCovering\">BumpCovering</a> <span class=\"fn\">ι</span> <span class=\"fn\">M</span> <span class=\"fn\">s</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hf</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>), <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Geometry/Manifold/ContMDiff/Defs.html#ContMDiff\">ContMDiff</a> <span class=\"fn\">I</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Geometry/Manifold/IsManifold/Basic.html#modelWithCornersSelf\">modelWithCornersSelf</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">↑<a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Notation.html#Top.top\">⊤</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">⇑<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span>)</span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Geometry/Manifold/PartitionOfUnity.html#SmoothPartitionOfUnity\">SmoothPartitionOfUnity</a> <span class=\"fn\">ι</span> <span class=\"fn\">I</span> <span class=\"fn\">M</span> <span class=\"fn\">s</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A `BumpCovering` such that all functions in this covering are smooth generates a smooth\npartition of unity.\n\nIn our formalization, not every `f : BumpCovering ι M s` with smooth functions `f i` is a\n`SmoothBumpCovering`; instead, a `SmoothBumpCovering` is a covering by supports of\n`SmoothBumpFunction`s. So, we define `BumpCovering.toSmoothPartitionOfUnity`, then reuse it\nin `SmoothBumpCovering.toSmoothPartitionOfUnity`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Geometry/Manifold/PartitionOfUnity.html#BumpCovering.toSmoothPartitionOfUnity","kind":"def","line":311,"name":"BumpCovering.toSmoothPartitionOfUnity","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Geometry